The News Agency of Nigeria reports that the Kaduna State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, confirmed the incident in a statement on Saturday. At least one bandit has been killed in an encounter by troops of Sector Four of Operation Whirl Punch and Special Forces of the 167 Battalion of the Nigerian Army when the troops cleared a bandit hideout in Kaduna State.  The News Agency of Nigeria reports that the Kaduna State Commissioner for Internal Security and Home Affairs, Samuel Aruwan, confirmed the incident in a statement on Saturday.  According to the commissioner, the troops embarked on a long range fighting patrol to Tukurua general area in the Chikun Local Government Area of the state where they engaged and overpowered the terrorists and killed one of them during a gun battle.  Aruwan said, “The troops during the operation rescued 14 kidnap victims, comprising nine men and five women.  “The victims were moved to a secure location for debriefing and examination before being reunited with their families,” adding that the troops destroyed several camps while “two motorcycles were recovered during the operation.”  Aruwan stated that the state governor, Nasir El-Rufai applauded the troops’ successes and commended the leadership of the General Officer Commanding 1 Division, Maj.-Gen Taoreed Lagbaja and the Force Commander of Operation Whirl Punch.    --